iaspora theory about the complex relation between the local and transnational and the enduring effects of slavery. Reflecting on the ethics of narration, this study is particularly attentive to the risks of representing anti-black violence and to the intricacies involved in (re-)appropriating slavery's archive.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2017: Backlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAfrican Diaspora Studies. 4aAmerica. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aAnti-Black Violence. 4aBlack Feminist Studies. 4aCanada. 4aCultural Studies. 4aGhana. 4aJamaica. 4aLawrence Hill. 4aMarlon James. 4aMemory Culture. 4aNeo-Slave Narratives. 4aPostcolonialism. 4aRace. 4aSaidiya Hartman. 4aSouth Africa. 4aToni Morrison. 4aU.S.A. 4aYvette Christiansë. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAfrican Diaspora Studies.  aAmerica.  aAmerican Studies.  aAnti-Black Violence.  aBlack Feminist Studies.  aCanada.  aCultural Studies.  aGhana.  aJamaica.  aLawrence Hill.  aMarlon James.  aMemory Culture.  aNeo-Slave Narratives.  aPostcolonialism.  aRace.  aSaidiya Hartman.  aSouth Africa.  aToni Morrison.  aU.S.A.  aYvette Christiansë.2 aKnowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2017: Backlist Collectionefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2016z9783110485257oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part o